================================================================================
TECHNICAL STACK
================================================================================

Frontend:
- Vanilla HTML/CSS/JavaScript (NO frameworks, < 25KB)
- Web Speech API (built-in browser, zero cost)
- CSS animations & responsive design
- Tailwind CSS via CDN (optional enhancement)

Browser APIs Used:
- getUserMedia (microphone access)
- SpeechRecognition (speech-to-text)
- SpeechSynthesisUtterance (text-to-speech)
- Fetch API (backend communication)
- LocalStorage (optional persistence)

Backend Reference:
- Node.js + Express.js
- CORS middleware
- JSON payload handling
- Ready for OpenClaw gateway integration

================================================================================
HOW TO TEST
================================================================================

1. LOCAL BROWSER:
   - Open: /openclaw/workspace/canvas-apps/voice-chat/index.html
   - Browser will prompt for microphone access
   - Click "Start Listening"
   - Speak: "Hello"
   - See transcription + fallback response

2. WITH BACKEND:
   - Run: node backend-example.js
   - Connect frontend to localhost:3000
   - Full conversation flow (voice → text → response → speech)

3. CANVAS INTEGRATION:
   - Command: canvas present --url file:///openclaw/workspace/canvas-apps/voice-chat/index.html
   - Or integrate with OpenClaw session via canvas eval

4. MOBILE:
   - Open on iOS Safari or Android Chrome
   - Same flow as desktop
   - Responsive design adapts

